casebody.data:
PEOPLE
v.
PADILLA S239454 Supreme Court of California. JUNE 13, 2018 Votes: Cantil-Sakauye, C.J., Chin, Corrigan, Liu, Cuéllar and Kruger, JJ.

The above-captioned matter is dismissed as moot in light of Senate Bill No. 394, signed into law on October 11, 2017. The matter is remanded to the Court of Appeal, Second Appellate District, Division Four with directions to remand to the trial court for further proceedings. ( Cal. Rules of Court, rule 8.528(b).)
